{"parentUuid":"96c2f9bf-722e-49d1-bc0b-e3bb6a5af79a","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"a1c2c54165786c44c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Jb31HWu4Zi2nYyVX44xJy1","type":"tool_result","content":"3:--- a/.gitignore\n15:--- a/PROJECT.md\n18:-Feature: usage CSV export.\n19:-- GET /v1/usage/export returns the caller's usage rollups (customer_id, metric, window_start, total_quantity) as CSV.\n20:-- Existing API-key auth applies. No behavior change to any existing endpoint.\n29:--- a/docs/system_architecture.md\n35:-admin-set per-customer, per-metric usage caps (\"quotas\"). Four authenticated\n36:-HTTP endpoints, one PostgreSQL database, one Redis rate-limit store, running\n37:-as a Docker container on ECS Fargate behind an ALB.\n112:-  an ingest key does, plus call `PUT /v1/quotas`; a tenant that wants quotas\n113:-  provisions one admin-scoped key and uses it for both.\n123:-key for `PUT /v1/quotas`, including the DAST-context admin test key, DAST-3).\n131:--- a/src/api/README.md\n137:-| `routes/quotas.py` | `PUT /v1/quotas` handler; composes auth -> Tier-2 throttle -> an `admin`-scope gate (403 `forbidden` otherwise) -> `quota_service.upsert_tenant_quota`. |\n143:-| `schemas/quotas.py` | Pydantic models for PUT /v1/quotas request (`customer_id`, `metric`, `limit_per_window`, `extra='forbid'`) and response (echo shape). |\n146:-| `middleware.py` | Request-ID / trace-ID assignment, security headers (HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options), CORS (allows GET/POST/PUT). |\n160:-- `PUT /v1/quotas` from a non-`admin`-scoped key → 403 `forbidden` (function-level authorization, checked in the route's composed dependency).\n168:--- a/src/api/middleware.py\n174:-        allow_methods=[\"GET\", \"POST\", \"PUT\"],\n180:--- a/src/api/routes/quotas.py\n183:-\"\"\"`PUT /v1/quotas` — admin-scoped create-or-replace of a per-customer,\n184:-per-metric usage cap.\n189:-inherited from the middleware stack; this route wires\n193:-pattern (kept per-route, not shared, per the existing convention).\n199:-from fastapi import APIRouter, Depends, HTTPException, Request, Response, status\n202:-from src.api.schemas.quotas import QuotaPutRequest, QuotaResponse\n210:-from src.services.quota_service import to_response, upsert_tenant_quota\n248:--- a/src/api/schemas/quotas.py\n272:--- a/src/repositories/README.md\n278:-| `quotas_repo.py` | `upsert_quota(...)` — `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT (api_key_id, customer_id, metric) DO UPDATE ... RETURNING (xmax = 0) AS inserted`, reporting create-vs-replace in one round-trip. `read_tenant_quota_state_locked(...)` — the atomic check-then-decide: locks the quota row (`FOR UPDATE`), then reads the current-window rollup total as a **separate, fresh** statement (see *Notes* below for why). Returns `None` when no quota exists (unlimited, no lock taken). |\n286:-- `quotas_repo` is imported by both `quota_service` (the upsert) and `events_service` (the read-and-decide).\n313:--- a/src/repositories/quotas_repo.py\n394:--- a/src/services/README.md\n400:-| `quota_service.py` | `upsert_tenant_quota(principal, payload)` — create-or-replaces the caller's cap for `(customer_id, metric)` in one transaction; maps the repository's insert-vs-replace signal to 201/200 and logs the `quota.upsert` audit event. |\n409:-- `quota_service` imports `src/repositories.quotas_repo` to upsert the cap.\n410:-- All services receive an authenticated `AuthenticatedPrincipal` from the route handler (set by `require_api_key` guard); `principal.scope` gates `PUT /v1/quotas` at the route layer before `quota_service` ever runs (the export has no scope gate — any authenticated key may export its own tenant's data).\n426:--- a/src/services/quota_service.py\n429:-\"\"\"Service for `PUT /v1/quotas` — the admin-scoped upsert + 201/200 mapping.\n433:-Orchestrates one transaction per request: the `xmax` upsert in\n434:-`src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` reports create-vs-replace in a single\n435:-round-trip, so this layer only maps that to the HTTP status and emits the\n436:-audit-trail log (`quota.upsert`, plan §\"Repudiation\").\n446:-from src.api.schemas.quotas import QuotaPutRequest, QuotaResponse\n453:-from src.repositories.quotas_repo import upsert_quota\n511:--- a/tests/README.md\n517:-| `test_schemas_quotas.py` | Validation-contract tests for `QuotaPutRequest` (anchored `customer_id`/`metric` allowlists, `limit_per_window` bounds, injection rejection). |\n524:--- a/tests/integration/README.md\n530:-| `test_quotas_rls_backstop.py` | Adversarial proof that the `quotas_tenant_isolation` RLS policy alone (connecting as a `NOBYPASSRLS` role, primary `api_key_id` filter removed) still confines reads/updates to the caller's own tenant, and fails closed when the tenant context is unset. |\n538:--- a/tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py\n616:--- a/tests/test_schemas_quotas.py\n619:-\"\"\"Validation-contract tests for `QuotaPutRequest` (AC5, AC18).\"\"\"\n628:-from src.api.schemas.quotas import QuotaPutRequest","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"68ade20c-909a-4b42-9166-d5fd673ab3a5","timestamp":"2026-07-10T04:03:47.310Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"96c2f9bf-722e-49d1-bc0b-e3bb6a5af79a","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
