{"parentUuid":"4ac07b33-0ad0-4e33-b04b-e17818b67912","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"a1c2c54165786c44c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VfppQeo3bf3ZJmHKLCsera","type":"tool_result","content":"tests\\integration\\README.md:26:[Omitted long matching line]\ntests\\integration\\README.md:27:| `test_quotas_rls_backstop.py` | Adversarial proof that the `quotas_tenant_isolation` RLS policy alone (connecting as a `NOBYPASSRLS` role, primary `api_key_id` filter removed) still confines reads/updates/deletes to the caller's own tenant, and fails closed when the tenant context is unset. `test_rls_blocks_cross_tenant_delete_when_app_filter_is_absent` (new, quota-admin feature) is the DELETE-specific backstop proof, mirroring the existing read/update cases. |\ntests\\test_schemas_quotas.py:130:    schema boundary and never reaches the DELETE SQL sink.\"\"\"\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_rls_backstop.py:49:            text(f\"GRANT SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE ON quotas TO {role_name}\")\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_rls_backstop.py:136:    \"\"\"AC8/AC15 backstop proof for the quota-admin feature's new `DELETE\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_rls_backstop.py:140:    still confine a `NOBYPASSRLS` session's DELETE to only its own tenant's\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_rls_backstop.py:141:    row -- tenant B's row must survive an unfiltered DELETE issued under\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_rls_backstop.py:172:            # No api_key_id predicate at all -- mirrors delete_quota's DELETE\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_rls_backstop.py:175:                text(\"DELETE FROM quotas WHERE customer_id = 'rls_del_cust' RETURNING api_key_id\")\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_rls_backstop.py:179:            \"an unfiltered DELETE under tenant A's session setting must only \"\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_rls_backstop.py:195:        assert survivor[\"limit_per_window\"] == 2000, \"tenant B's row must survive the cross-tenant DELETE\"\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_list_delete.py:1:\"\"\"Integration tests for `GET /v1/quotas` (list) and `DELETE /v1/quotas`\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_list_delete.py:21:    the new GET/DELETE behavior.\"\"\"\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_list_delete.py:104:    \"\"\"AC6: DELETE of an existing quota -> 204 empty body; the row is gone\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_list_delete.py:134:    \"\"\"AC7: DELETE of a (customer_id, metric) with no quota -> 404 not_found,\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_list_delete.py:207:    \"\"\"AC10: an ingest-scoped key gets 403 `forbidden` on DELETE.\"\"\"\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_list_delete.py:221:    \"\"\"AC11: missing/malformed auth -> 401 on DELETE.\"\"\"\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_list_delete.py:236:    \"\"\"AC12: both GET and DELETE /v1/quotas are Tier-2 per-api_key_id rate\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_list_delete.py:320:    assert rollup_after == 5, \"DELETE must never touch usage_rollup\"\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_list_delete.py:338:    \"\"\"AC16: a successful DELETE logs `quota.delete` INFO (customer_id\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_list_delete.py:339:    redacted); a scope-denied GET or DELETE logs the existing `quota.forbidden` WARNING.\"\"\"\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_list_delete.py:356:    DELETE /v1/quotas, matching the implemented routes/schemas.\"\"\"\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_list_delete.py:401:    \"\"\"AC19: a forced internal error during DELETE returns the generic 500\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_list_delete.py:448:    assert row[\"limit_per_window\"] == 42, \"a failed DELETE must leave the target row intact (fail-closed)\"\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_list_delete.py:454:    \"\"\"AC6/AC7 under contention: N concurrent DELETE requests for the exact\ntests\\integration\\test_quotas_list_delete.py:458:    (delete_quota's single parameterized DELETE ... RETURNING) is actually"}]},"uuid":"b59cea73-ae86-4851-acd4-290af3672462","timestamp":"2026-07-10T04:04:01.887Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"4ac07b33-0ad0-4e33-b04b-e17818b67912","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"b59cea73-ae86-4851-acd4-290af3672462","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a1c2c54165786c44c","message":{"model":"claude-fable-5","id":"msg_011CcsiLQECVeLFQFokE8phb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LzB5d9DyYLZZUcc6R79R8t","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\routes\\quotas.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3258,"cache_read_input_tokens":36168,"output_tokens":751,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3258},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":751,"cache_read_input_tokens":36168,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3258,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3258,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsiLPJteaTLFzR3LDPsC","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","attributionSkill":"code-review","type":"assistant","uuid":"3c6fe86a-451d-497a-92ad-79b289318ced","timestamp":"2026-07-10T04:04:02.038Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"3c6fe86a-451d-497a-92ad-79b289318ced","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"a1c2c54165786c44c","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LzB5d9DyYLZZUcc6R79R8t","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"`/v1/quotas` — admin-scoped create-or-replace (`PUT`), list (`GET`), and\n2\tremove (`DELETE`) of a per-customer, per-metric usage cap.\n3\t\n4\tEdge behavior (security headers, CORS, body-size guard, Tier-1 throttle) is\n5\tinherited from the middleware stack; every route on this router wires\n6\tauth -> Tier-2 throttle -> admin-scope check -> schema validation -> service,\n7\tmirroring the `events`/`usage` routes' sibling `_require_authenticated_and_throttled`\n8\tpattern (kept per-route, not shared, per the existing convention). All three\n9\tverbs depend on the same `_require_admin_and_throttled` chain — GET/DELETE\n10\treuse it verbatim rather than introducing a new scope or auth path.\n11\t\"\"\"\n12\t\n13\tfrom typing import Annotated\n14\t\n15\tfrom fastapi import APIRouter, Depends, HTTPException, Query, Request, Response, status\n16\t\n17\tfrom src.api.schemas.quotas import QuotaDeleteParams, QuotaPutRequest, QuotaResponse\n18\tfrom src.auth import require_api_key\n19\tfrom src.auth.api_key import AuthenticatedPrincipal\n20\tfrom src.auth.rate_limit import enforce_tier2_rate_limit\n21\tfrom src.logging import get_logger\n22\tfrom src.services.quota_service import (\n23\t    delete_tenant_quota,\n24\t    list_tenant_quotas,\n25\t    to_response,\n26\t    upsert_tenant_quota,\n27\t)\n28\t\n29\trouter = APIRouter(tags=[\"quotas\"])\n30\tlogger = get_logger(service=\"meterly\")\n31\t\n32\t_ADMIN_SCOPE = \"admin\"\n33\t\n34\t\n35\tasync def _require_admin_and_throttled(\n36\t    request: Request, principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal = Depends(require_api_key)\n37\t) -> AuthenticatedPrincipal:\n38\t    \"\"\"Compose auth, then the Tier-2 per-key throttle, then the admin-scope\n39\t    gate, in that order — mirrors `src/api/routes/events.py`'s dependency\n40\t    chain, extended with the function-level authorization check this route\n41\t    alone requires (ASVS 8.2.1).\n42\t    \"\"\"\n43\t    await enforce_tier2_rate_limit(request, principal)\n44\t    if principal.scope != _ADMIN_SCOPE:\n45\t        logger.warning(\n46\t            \"quota.forbidden\",\n47\t            userId=principal.api_key_id,\n48\t            action=\"deny\",\n49\t            reason=\"insufficient_scope\",\n50\t        )\n51\t        raise HTTPException(status_code=status.HTTP_403_FORBIDDEN, detail=\"admin scope required\")\n52\t    return principal\n53\t\n54\t\n55\t@router.put(\"/v1/quotas\", response_model=QuotaResponse)\n56\tasync def put_quota(\n57\t    payload: QuotaPutRequest,\n58\t    response: Response,\n59\t    principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal = Depends(_require_admin_and_throttled),\n60\t) -> QuotaResponse:\n61\t    \"\"\"Create or replace the cap for `(customer_id, metric)` under the\n62\t    caller's own tenant — 201 on create, 200 on replace.\"\"\"\n63\t    outcome = await upsert_tenant_quota(principal, payload)\n64\t    response.status_code = outcome.http_status\n65\t    return to_response(outcome)\n66\t\n67\t\n68\t@router.get(\"/v1/quotas\", response_model=list[QuotaResponse])\n69\tasync def list_quotas_endpoint(\n70\t    principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal = Depends(_require_admin_and_throttled),\n71\t) -> list[QuotaResponse]:\n72\t    \"\"\"Return the caller's own tenant's full, unpaginated quota list,\n73\t    deterministically ordered by `(customer_id, metric)`. An empty tenant\n74\t    gets `200 []`, never a 404.\"\"\"\n75\t    return await list_tenant_quotas(principal)\n76\t\n77\t\n78\t@router.delete(\"/v1/quotas\", status_code=status.HTTP_204_NO_CONTENT)\n79\tasync def delete_quota_endpoint(\n80\t    params: Annotated[QuotaDeleteParams, Query()],\n81\t    principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal = Depends(_require_admin_and_throttled),\n82\t) -> Response:\n83\t    \"\"\"Remove the cap for `(customer_id, metric)` under the caller's own\n84\t    tenant — 204 on success, 404 if no such quota exists in this tenant\n85\t    (explicit, not silently idempotent).\"\"\"\n86\t    await delete_tenant_quota(principal, params)\n87\t    return Response(status_code=status.HTTP_204_NO_CONTENT)\n88\t"}]},"uuid":"17e060e9-eea4-40eb-ac1a-17a0c058ae45","timestamp":"2026-07-10T04:04:02.065Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"3c6fe86a-451d-497a-92ad-79b289318ced","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
